Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
La Palma substation is a ± 5.03 acre lot with several structures on sites. The main building is a ± 10,579 square foot office building built in 1991 that also has a warehouse component to it, with the second floor.
Across the parking lot sits a warehouse totaling ± 7,800 square feet built in 1991 and 2010. Two awning areas totaling ± 3,540 square feet can also be found on site. Construction is brick exterior wall in main building, with metal construction on the warehouse section, as well as metal construction on the ± 7,800 square foot building adjacent to the main building.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in University Business Park, this building is situated less than 1/2 mile from the amenities of IH-10 and in a bustling corporate campus setting. A new roof was installed in 2012 and the HVAC was replaced in 2019.  

Additionally, new interior improvements by the tenant include a gym and open office areas with exposed ducting. The building is currently used as headquarters location with office and light fabrication capabilities. Large floor plates provide flexibility if a multi-tenant option is desired.
